It does not matter how many people demand it, it will not happen in Angola", said Eduardo dos Santos (Berson 2019).
Stiff Anti-Abortion Laws and Abortion Restrictions
In general, abortion is illegal under the Penal Code in all other situations, except for cases of rape, incest, fetal malformations. The government of Angola may have progressive policies on some women’s health issues, such as
contraception, but it remains fundamentally restrictive on others, such as abortion. There are certain types of legislative processes that are best suited for cases of reproductive health policy making. Such processes should not be applied in the process of addressing issues of women’s abortion rights.
The first legal provision which punishes abortion is article 35, under the code called" Delicts Against the Incumbencies of Maternity" and that is written in accordance with the Portuguese Penal Code, under the law of 1886. When a woman has an abortion, the penalty is two years in prison. The judge also has the possibility of prohibiting the activity of the person who has committed the abortion (Corlea 2010).
